        Returns a masked version of the card number based on the provided settings.
        Parameters:
        cardNumber - A card number.
        maskCharacter - The character used in the mask, if not provided takes '*' by default.
        cardFormat - CCConsumerMaskFormat The formatted object used for masking. If not provided takes CCConsumerMaskFormat.CARD_MASK_LAST_FOUR by default.
        Returns:

      • consumerMaxCardLengthForCardNumber

        public static int consumerMaxCardLengthForCardNumber(@NonNull
                                                     java.lang.String cardNumber)
        Returns the max length for the determined card issuer of the number. If the issuer cannot be determined, `-1` is returned.
        Uses getIssuerFromCardNumber(String) to determine the card issuer.
        Parameters:
        cardNumber - A card number.
        Returns:
        An integer representing the max length for the card's determined issuer.

      • validateCardLength

        public static boolean validateCardLength(@NonNull
                                         java.lang.String cardNumber)
        Validates card number length is in acceptable bounds for card issuer. If issuer cannot be determined, false is returned.
        Uses getIssuerFromCardNumber(String) to determine the card issuer.
        Parameters:
        cardNumber - A card number.
        Returns:
        true if the card is an acceptable length for the determined card issuer, false otherwise.

      • validateCardNumber

        public static boolean validateCardNumber(java.lang.String cardNumber)
        Runs some simple validation on the card number.
        This is the order of functions it uses to validate the card number: - Get card issuer getIssuerFromCardNumber(String) - Validate card number length validateCardLength(String) - Luhn validation CCCLuhnCheck
        Parameters:
        cardNumber - A card number.
        Returns:
        true If the card number is valid.
